nnMultipleSpanningTreeMib.name: nnMultipleSpanningTreeMib

revisions.description: v005: instanceUp, instanceDown notifications added to nnMstGenNotificationType object.

nnMstNoOfInstancesSupported.name: nnMstNoOfInstancesSupported
nnMstNoOfInstancesSupported.description: Indicates Maximum number of spanning tree Instances supported.

nnMstMaxHopCount.name: nnMstMaxHopCount
nnMstMaxHopCount.description: Indicates the Maximum Hop Count value. The granularity of this timer is specified to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

nnMstBrgAddress.name: nnMstBrgAddress
nnMstBrgAddress.description: The MAC address used by this bridge when it must be referred to in a unique fashion. It is recommended that this be the numerically smallest MAC address of all ports that belong to this bridge. However it is only required to be unique. When concatenated with nnMstCistBridgePriority or nnMstBridgePriority a unique BridgeIdentifier is formed which is used in the Spanning Tree Protocol.

nnMstCistRoot.name: nnMstCistRoot
nnMstCistRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the Root of the common spanning tree as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the CIST Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

nnMstCistRegionalRoot.name: nnMstCistRegionalRoot
nnMstCistRegionalRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the Root of the Multiple spanning tree region as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node. This value is used as the CIST Regional Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node.

nnMstCistRootCost.name: nnMstCistRootCost
nnMstCistRootCost.description: The Cost of the path to the CIST Root as seen from this bridge.

nnMstCistRegionalRootCost.name: nnMstCistRegionalRootCost
nnMstCistRegionalRootCost.description: The Cost of the path to the CIST Regional Root as seen from this bridge.

nnMstCistRootPort.name: nnMstCistRootPort
nnMstCistRootPort.description: The Port Number of the Port which offers the lowest path cost from this bridge to the CIST Root Bridge.

nnMstCistBridgePriority.name: nnMstCistBridgePriority
nnMstCistBridgePriority.description: The Value of the writable portion of the Bridge Identifier comprising of the first two octets. The values that are set for Bridge Priority must be in steps of 4096.

nnMstCistBridgeMaxAge.name: nnMstCistBridgeMaxAge
nnMstCistBridgeMaxAge.description: The value that all bridges use for MaxAge when this bridge is acting as the root. The granularity of this timer is specified to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

nnMstCistBridgeForwardDelay.name: nnMstCistBridgeForwardDelay
nnMstCistBridgeForwardDelay.description: The value that all bridges use for ForwardDelay when this bridge is acting as the root. Note that 802.1D specifies that the range for this parameter is related to the value of BridgeMaxAge. The granularity of this timer is specified to be 1 second. An agent may return a badValue error if a set is attempted to a value which is not a whole number of seconds.

nnMstCistHoldTime.name: nnMstCistHoldTime
nnMstCistHoldTime.description: This time value determines the interval length during which no more than two Configuration bridge PDUs shall be transmitted by this node, in units of hundredths of a second.

nnMstCistMaxAge.name: nnMstCistMaxAge
nnMstCistMaxAge.description: The maximum age of Spanning Tree Protocol information learned from the network on any port before it is discarded, in units of hundredths of a second. This is the actual value that this bridge is currently using.

nnMstCistForwardDelay.name: nnMstCistForwardDelay
nnMstCistForwardDelay.description: This time value, measured in units of hundredths of a second, controls how fast a port changes its spanning state when moving towards the Forwarding state. The value determines how long the port stays in a particular state before moving to the next state.

nnMstMstpUpCount.name: nnMstMstpUpCount
nnMstMstpUpCount.description: The number of times MSTP Module has been enabled. A Trap is generated on the occurence of this event.

nnMstMstpDownCount.name: nnMstMstpDownCount
nnMstMstpDownCount.description: The number of times MSTP Module has been disabled. A Trap is generated on the occurence of this event.

nnMstPathCostDefaultType.name: nnMstPathCostDefaultType
nnMstPathCostDefaultType.description: The version of the Spanning Tree default Path Costs that are to be used by this Bridge. A value of 8021d1998(1) uses the 16-bit default Path Costs from IEEE Std. 802.1D-1998. A value of stp8021t2001(2) uses the 32-bit default Path Costs from IEEE Std. 802.1t.

nnMstForceProtocolVersion.name: nnMstForceProtocolVersion
nnMstForceProtocolVersion.description: The version of Spanning Tree Protocol the bridge is currently running. The value 'stpCompatible(0)' indicates the Spanning Tree Protocol specified in IEEE 802.1D and 'rstp(2)' indicates the Rapid Spanning Tree Protocol specified in IEEE 802.1w and 'mstp(3)' indicates the Multiple Spanning Tree Protocol Specified in IEEE 802.1s.

nnMstTxHoldCount.name: nnMstTxHoldCount
nnMstTxHoldCount.description: The value used by the Port Transmit state machine to limit the maximum transmission rate.

nnMstConfigIdSel.name: nnMstConfigIdSel
nnMstConfigIdSel.description: The Configuration Identifier Format Selector used by the Bridge. This has a fixed value of 0 to indicate RegionName, RegionVersion are specified as in Standard.

nnMstRegionName.name: nnMstRegionName
nnMstRegionName.description: The Name for the Region's configuration. By Default Region Name will be equal to the Bridge Mac Address.

nnMstConfigDigest.name: nnMstConfigDigest
nnMstConfigDigest.description: The Configuration Digest value for this Region, this is an MD5 digest value, and hence must always be 16 octets long.

nnMstRegionConfigChangeCount.name: nnMstRegionConfigChangeCount
nnMstRegionConfigChangeCount.description: The number of times a Region Configuration Identifier Change was detected. A Trap is generated on the occurence of this event.

nnMstCistBridgeRoleSelectionSemState.name: nnMstCistBridgeRoleSelectionSemState
nnMstCistBridgeRoleSelectionSemState.description: Current state of the Port Role Selection State Machine of this bridge in Common Spanning Tree context

nnMstCistTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: nnMstCistTimeSinceTopologyChange
nnMstCistTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the TcWhile Timer for any port in this Bridge was non-zero for Common Spanning Tree context.

nnMstCistTopChanges.name: nnMstCistTopChanges
nnMstCistTopChanges.description: The number of times that there have been atleast one non-zero TcWhile Timer on this Bridge for Common Spanning Tree context.

nnMstCistNewRootBridgeCount.name: nnMstCistNewRootBridgeCount
nnMstCistNewRootBridgeCount.description: The number of times this Bridge has detected a Root Bridge change for Common Spanning Tree context. A Trap is generated on the occurence of this event.

nnMstBridgeTable.name: nnMstBridgeTable
nnMstBridgeTable.description: Table containing Bridge Information specific to Spanning Tree Instance.

nnMstBridgeInstance.name: nnMstBridgeInstance
nnMstBridgeInstance.description: Spanning Tree Instance to which the information belongs.

nnMstBridgeRegionalRoot.name: nnMstBridgeRegionalRoot
nnMstBridgeRegionalRoot.description: MSTI Regional Root Identifier value for the Instance. This value is used as the MSTI Regional Root Identifier parameter in all Configuration Bridge PDUs originated by this node

nnMstBridgePriority.name: nnMstBridgePriority
nnMstBridgePriority.description: The writable portion of the MSTI Bridge Identifier. comprising of the first two octets. The values that are set for Bridge Priority must be in steps of 4096.

nnMstBridgeRootCost.name: nnMstBridgeRootCost
nnMstBridgeRootCost.description: The Cost of the path to the MSTI Regional Root as seen by this bridge.

nnMstBridgeRootPort.name: nnMstBridgeRootPort
nnMstBridgeRootPort.description: The Port Number of the Port which offers the lowest path cost from this bridge to the MSTI Region Root Bridge.

nnMstBridgeTimeSinceTopologyChange.name: nnMstBridgeTimeSinceTopologyChange
nnMstBridgeTimeSinceTopologyChange.description: The time (in hundredths of a second) since the TcWhile Timer for any port in this Bridge was non-zero for this spanning tree instance.

nnMstBridgeTopChanges.name: nnMstBridgeTopChanges
nnMstBridgeTopChanges.description: The number of times that there have been atleast one non-zero TcWhile Timer on this Bridge for this spanning tree instance.

nnMstBridgeNewRootCount.name: nnMstBridgeNewRootCount
nnMstBridgeNewRootCount.description: The number of times this Bridge has detected a Root Bridge change for this spanning tree instance. A Trap is generated on the occurence of this event.

nnMstBridgeRoleSelectionSemState.name: nnMstBridgeRoleSelectionSemState
nnMstBridgeRoleSelectionSemState.description: Current state of the Port Role Selection State Machine for this spanning tree instance for this bridge.

nnMstBridgeInstanceUpCount.name: nnMstBridgeInstanceUpCount
nnMstBridgeInstanceUpCount.description: The number of times a new spanning tree instance has been created. A Trap is generated on the occurence of this event.

nnMstBridgeInstanceDownCount.name: nnMstBridgeInstanceDownCount
nnMstBridgeInstanceDownCount.description: The number of times a spanning tree instance has been deleted. A Trap is generated on the occurence of this event.

nnMstBridgeOldDesignatedRoot.name: nnMstBridgeOldDesignatedRoot
nnMstBridgeOldDesignatedRoot.description: The bridge identifier of the old root of the spanning tree instance as determined by the Spanning Tree Protocol as executed by this node.

nnMstBridgeEnabled.name: nnMstBridgeEnabled
nnMstBridgeEnabled.description: This object is used to control whether this bridge instance is enabled or disabled.

nnMstBridgeRowStatus.name: nnMstBridgeRowStatus
nnMstBridgeRowStatus.description: This object is used to control row creation/deletion.

nnMstCistPortTable.name: nnMstCistPortTable
nnMstCistPortTable.description: This table contains Common Spanning Tree Port Information.

nnMstCistPortEntry.name: nnMstCistPortEntry
nnMstCistPortEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every port for Common Spanning tree.

nnMstCistPort.name: nnMstCistPort
nnMstCistPort.description: The Port number of the port for which this entry contains spanning tree information.

nnMstCistPortPathCost.name: nnMstCistPortPathCost
nnMstCistPortPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the CIST Root which include this port.

nnMstCistPortPriority.name: nnMstCistPortPriority
nnMstCistPortPriority.description: The four most significant bits of the Port Identifier of the Spanning Tree instance can be modified by setting the CistPortPriority value. The values that are set for Port Priority must be in steps of 16.

nnMstCistPortDesignatedRoot.name: nnMstCistPortDesignatedRoot
nnMstCistPortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the bridge recorded as the CIST Root in the configuration BPDUs transmitted.

nnMstCistPortDesignatedBridge.name: nnMstCistPortDesignatedBridge
nnMstCistPortDesignatedBridge.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for the port's segment.

nnMstCistPortDesignatedPort.name: nnMstCistPortDesignatedPort
nnMstCistPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

nnMstCistPortAdminP2P.name: nnMstCistPortAdminP2P
nnMstCistPortAdminP2P.description: The administrative point-to-point status of the LAN segment attached to this port. A value of forceTrue(0) indicates that this port should always be treated as if it is connected to a point-to-point link. A value of forceFalse(1) indicates that this port should be treated as having a shared media connection. A value of auto(2) indicates that this port is considered to have a point-to-point link if it is an Aggregator and all of its members are aggregatable, or if the MAC entity is configured for full duplex operation, either through auto-negotiation or by management means.

nnMstCistPortOperP2P.name: nnMstCistPortOperP2P
nnMstCistPortOperP2P.description: The operational point-to-point status of the LAN segment attached to this port. It indicates whether a port is considered to have a point-to-point connection or not. The value is determined by management or by auto-detection, as described in the nnMstCistPortAdminP2P object.

nnMstCistPortAdminEdgeStatus.name: nnMstCistPortAdminEdgeStatus
nnMstCistPortAdminEdgeStatus.description: The administrative value of the Edge Port parameter. A value of TRUE(1) indicates that this port should be assumed as an edge-port and a value of FALSE(2) indicates that this port should be assumed as a non-edge-port.

nnMstCistPortOperEdgeStatus.name: nnMstCistPortOperEdgeStatus
nnMstCistPortOperEdgeStatus.description: The operational value of the Edge Port parameter. The object is initialized to the value of nnMstCistPortAdminEdgeStatus and is set FALSE on reception of a BPDU.

nnMstCistPortProtocolMigration.name: nnMstCistPortProtocolMigration
nnMstCistPortProtocolMigration.description: Indicates the Protocol migration state of this Port. When operating in RSTP/MSTP (version >= 2) mode, writing TRUE(1) to this object forces this port to transmit MSTP BPDUs without instance information. Any other operation on this object has no effect and it always returns FALSE(2) when read.

nnMstCistPortState.name: nnMstCistPortState
nnMstCistPortState.description: Current state of the Port as defined by the Common spanning tree protocol.

nnMstCistForcePortState.name: nnMstCistForcePortState
nnMstCistForcePortState.description: Current state of the Port which can be changed to either Disabled or Enabled for the base spanning tree instance.

nnMstCistPortForwardTransitions.name: nnMstCistPortForwardTransitions
nnMstCistPortForwardTransitions.description: Number of times this port has transitioned to the Forwarding State.

nnMstCistPortRxMstBpduCount.name: nnMstCistPortRxMstBpduCount
nnMstCistPortRxMstBpduCount.description: Number of MST BPDUs received on this port.

nnMstCistPortRxRstBpduCount.name: nnMstCistPortRxRstBpduCount
nnMstCistPortRxRstBpduCount.description: Number of RST BPDUs received on this port.

nnMstCistPortRxConfigBpduCount.name: nnMstCistPortRxConfigBpduCount
nnMstCistPortRxConfigBpduCount.description: Number of Configuration BPDUs received on this port.

nnMstCistPortRxTcnBpduCount.name: nnMstCistPortRxTcnBpduCount
nnMstCistPortRxTcnBpduCount.description: Number of TCN BPDUs received on this port.

nnMstCistPortTxMstBpduCount.name: nnMstCistPortTxMstBpduCount
nnMstCistPortTxMstBpduCount.description: Number of MST BPDUs Transmitted from this port.

nnMstCistPortTxRstBpduCount.name: nnMstCistPortTxRstBpduCount
nnMstCistPortTxRstBpduCount.description: Number of RST BPDUs Transmitted from this port.

nnMstCistPortTxConfigBpduCount.name: nnMstCistPortTxConfigBpduCount
nnMstCistPortTxConfigBpduCount.description: Number of Configuration BPDUs Transmitted from this port.

nnMstCistPortTxTcnBpduCount.name: nnMstCistPortTxTcnBpduCount
nnMstCistPortTxTcnBpduCount.description: Number of TCN BPDUs Transmitted from this port.

nnMstCistPortInvalidMstBpduRxCount.name: nnMstCistPortInvalidMstBpduRxCount
nnMstCistPortInvalidMstBpduRxCount.description: Number of Invalid MST BPDUs Received on this port.

nnMstCistPortInvalidRstBpduRxCount.name: nnMstCistPortInvalidRstBpduRxCount
nnMstCistPortInvalidRstBpduRxCount.description: Number of Invalid RST BPDUs Received on this port.

nnMstCistPortInvalidConfigBpduRxCount.name: nnMstCistPortInvalidConfigBpduRxCount
nnMstCistPortInvalidConfigBpduRxCount.description: Number of Invalid Configuration BPDUs Received on this port.

nnMstCistPortInvalidTcnBpduRxCount.name: nnMstCistPortInvalidTcnBpduRxCount
nnMstCistPortInvalidTcnBpduRxCount.description: Number of Invalid TCN BPDUs Received on this port.

nnMstCistPortTransmitSemState.name: nnMstCistPortTransmitSemState
nnMstCistPortTransmitSemState.description: Indicates current State of the Port Transmit state machine.

nnMstCistPortReceiveSemState.name: nnMstCistPortReceiveSemState
nnMstCistPortReceiveSemState.description: Indicates current State of the Port Receive state machine.

nnMstCistPortProtMigrationSemState.name: nnMstCistPortProtMigrationSemState
nnMstCistPortProtMigrationSemState.description: Indicates current State of the Port Protocol Migration State machine.

nnMstCistProtocolMigrationCount.name: nnMstCistProtocolMigrationCount
nnMstCistProtocolMigrationCount.description: The number of times this Port has migrated from one STP protocol version to another. The relevant protocols are STP-COMPATIBLE and RSTP/MSTP. A Trap is generated on the occurence of this event.

nnMstCistPortDesignatedCost.name: nnMstCistPortDesignatedCost
nnMstCistPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port.

nnMstCistPortRegionalRoot.name: nnMstCistPortRegionalRoot
nnMstCistPortRegionalRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the bridge recorded as the CIST Regional Root Identifier in the configuration BPDUs transmitted.

nnMstCistPortRegionalPathCost.name: nnMstCistPortRegionalPathCost
nnMstCistPortRegionalPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the CIST Regional Root which include this port.

nnMstCistSelectedPortRole.name: nnMstCistSelectedPortRole
nnMstCistSelectedPortRole.description: Selected Port Role of the port for this spanning tree instance.

nnMstCistCurrentPortRole.name: nnMstCistCurrentPortRole
nnMstCistCurrentPortRole.description: Current Port Role of the port for this spanning tree instance.

nnMstCistPortInfoSemState.name: nnMstCistPortInfoSemState
nnMstCistPortInfoSemState.description: Current state of the Port Information State Machine for this port in this spanning tree context.

nnMstCistPortRoleTransitionSemState.name: nnMstCistPortRoleTransitionSemState
nnMstCistPortRoleTransitionSemState.description: Current state of the Port Role Transition State Machine for this port in this spanning tree context.

nnMstCistPortStateTransitionSemState.name: nnMstCistPortStateTransitionSemState
nnMstCistPortStateTransitionSemState.description: Current state of the Port State Transition State Machine for this port in this spanning tree context.

nnMstCistPortTopologyChangeSemState.name: nnMstCistPortTopologyChangeSemState
nnMstCistPortTopologyChangeSemState.description: Current state of the Topology Change State Machine for this port in this spanning tree context.

nnMstCistPortHelloTime.name: nnMstCistPortHelloTime
nnMstCistPortHelloTime.description: The amount of time between the transmission of Configuration bridge PDUs by this node on this port in units of hundredths of a second.

nnMstCistPortOperVersion.name: nnMstCistPortOperVersion
nnMstCistPortOperVersion.description: This indicates whether the Port is operationally in the Mstp mode, Rstp mode or the Stp-compatible mode i.e., whether the Port is transmitting MST BPDUs, RST BPDUs or Config/TCN BPDUs.

nnMstCistPortEffectivePortState.name: nnMstCistPortEffectivePortState
nnMstCistPortEffectivePortState.description: The effective operational state of the port for CIST. This will TRUE only when the port is operationally up in the Interface level and Protocol level for CIST. This is will be set to False for all other times.

nnMstPortTable.name: nnMstPortTable
nnMstPortTable.description: This table contains Spanning Tree Instance Specific Port Information.

nnMstPortEntry.name: nnMstPortEntry
nnMstPortEntry.description: A list of information maintained by every port for each and every spanning tree instance.

nnMstPort.name: nnMstPort
nnMstPort.description: The Port number of the port for which this entry contains spanning tree information.

nnMstPortPathCost.name: nnMstPortPathCost
nnMstPortPathCost.description: The contribution of this port to the path cost of paths towards the MSTI Root which include this port.

nnMstPortPriority.name: nnMstPortPriority
nnMstPortPriority.description: The four most significant bits of the Port Identifier for a given Spanning Tree instance can be modified independently for each Spanning Tree instance supported by the Bridge. The values that are set for Port Priority must be in steps of 16.

nnMstPortDesignatedRoot.name: nnMstPortDesignatedRoot
nnMstPortDesignatedRoot.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the bridge recorded as the MSTI Regional Root in the configuration BPDUs transmitted.

nnMstPortDesignatedBridge.name: nnMstPortDesignatedBridge
nnMstPortDesignatedBridge.description: The unique Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for the port's segment.

nnMstPortDesignatedPort.name: nnMstPortDesignatedPort
nnMstPortDesignatedPort.description: The Port identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment.

nnMstPortState.name: nnMstPortState
nnMstPortState.description: Current state of the Port as defined by the Multiple spanning tree protocol. Port which is Forwarding state in one instance can be in Discarding (Blocking) state in another instance.

nnMstPortForcePortState.name: nnMstPortForcePortState
nnMstPortForcePortState.description: Current state of the Port which can be changed to either Disabled or Enabled for the specific spanning tree instance.

nnMstPortForwardTransitions.name: nnMstPortForwardTransitions
nnMstPortForwardTransitions.description: Number of times this port has transitioned to the Forwarding State for specific instance.

nnMstPortReceivedBPDUs.name: nnMstPortReceivedBPDUs
nnMstPortReceivedBPDUs.description: Number of BPDUs received by this port for this spanning tree instance.

nnMstPortTransmittedBPDUs.name: nnMstPortTransmittedBPDUs
nnMstPortTransmittedBPDUs.description: Number of BPDUs transmitted on this port for this spanning tree instance.

nnMstPortInvalidBPDUsRcvd.name: nnMstPortInvalidBPDUsRcvd
nnMstPortInvalidBPDUsRcvd.description: Number of Invalid BPDUs received on this Port for this spanning tree instance.

nnMstPortDesignatedCost.name: nnMstPortDesignatedCost
nnMstPortDesignatedCost.description: The path cost of the Designated Port of the segment connected to this port.

nnMstPortSelectedPortRole.name: nnMstPortSelectedPortRole
nnMstPortSelectedPortRole.description: Selected Port Role of the port for this spanning tree instance.

nnMstPortCurrentPortRole.name: nnMstPortCurrentPortRole
nnMstPortCurrentPortRole.description: Current Port Role of the port for this spanning tree instance.

nnMstPortInfoSemState.name: nnMstPortInfoSemState
nnMstPortInfoSemState.description: Current state of the Port Information State Machine for this port in this spanning tree context.

nnMstPortRoleTransitionSemState.name: nnMstPortRoleTransitionSemState
nnMstPortRoleTransitionSemState.description: Current state of the Port Role Transition State Machine for this port in this spanning tree context.

nnMstPortStateTransitionSemState.name: nnMstPortStateTransitionSemState
nnMstPortStateTransitionSemState.description: Current state of the Port State Transition State Machine for this port in this spanning tree context.

nnMstPortTopologyChangeSemState.name: nnMstPortTopologyChangeSemState
nnMstPortTopologyChangeSemState.description: Current state of the Topology Change State Machine for this port in this spanning tree context.

nnMstPortEffectivePortState.name: nnMstPortEffectivePortState
nnMstPortEffectivePortState.description: The effective operational stae of the port for specific instance. This is will be TRUE only when the port is operationally up in the interface level and Protocol level for the specific instance. This is will be set to false at all other times.

nnMstSetNotifications.name: nnMstSetNotifications
nnMstSetNotifications.description: This object is used to enable and disable specific MSTP traps. Currently the following are defined 0 - Notifications are not enabled. 1 - General Notifications like protocol up or down 2 - Exception Notifications like memory failure or buffer failure or port protocol migration or invalid packet rcvd in port 3 - All the above Notifications

nnMstGenNotificationType.name: nnMstGenNotificationType
nnMstGenNotificationType.description: The general events like none - none of the below values up - protocol UP, down - protocol DOWN instanceUp - MSTP instance enabled instanceDown - MSTP instance disabled

nnMstErrNotificationType.name: nnMstErrNotificationType
nnMstErrNotificationType.description: The error event like none - none of the below values memfail - memory allocation failure bufffail - buffer allocation failure

nnMstPortNotificationTable.name: nnMstPortNotificationTable
nnMstPortNotificationTable.description: This table is used to store the notification information occured in each of the port for protocol migration and invalid packet received

nnMstPortNotificationEntry.name: nnMstPortNotificationEntry
nnMstPortNotificationEntry.description: This entry is used to store the notification information

nnMstPortNotificationIndex.name: nnMstPortNotificationIndex
nnMstPortNotificationIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, indicating the Port number.

nnMstPortNotificationMigrationType.name: nnMstPortNotificationMigrationType
nnMstPortNotificationMigrationType.description: Port Protocol migration type occured in the port

nnMstPortNotificationPktErrType.name: nnMstPortNotificationPktErrType
nnMstPortNotificationPktErrType.description: Type of invalid packet received in each of the port

nnMstPortNotificationPktErrVal.name: nnMstPortNotificationPktErrVal
nnMstPortNotificationPktErrVal.description: Packet error value corresponding to the above type

nnMstGeneralEvent.name: nnMstGeneralEvent
nnMstGeneralEvent.description: Generated when any of the general events like protocol up or protocol down occurs

nnMstErrorEvent.name: nnMstErrorEvent
nnMstErrorEvent.description: Generated when any of the error events like memory failure or buffer failure or protocol migration or new root or topology change occurs

nnMstNewRoot.name: nnMstNewRoot
nnMstNewRoot.description: Generated whenever a new root bridge is selected in the topology

nnMstTopologyChange.name: nnMstTopologyChange
nnMstTopologyChange.description: Generated when topology change is detected

nnMstProtocolMigration.name: nnMstProtocolMigration
nnMstProtocolMigration.description: Generated when port protocol migration happens in the port

nnMstRegionConfigChange.name: nnMstRegionConfigChange
nnMstRegionConfigChange.description: Generated when the MST region's configuration identifier changes.

nnMstBridgeVlanMapTable.name: nnMstBridgeVlanMapTable
nnMstBridgeVlanMapTable.description: Table containing Mapped VlanList specific to Spanning Tree Instance.

nnMstBridgeVlanMapEntry.name: nnMstBridgeVlanMapEntry
nnMstBridgeVlanMapEntry.description: Entry indicating the Bridge VlanMap Information.

nnMstBridgeInstId.name: nnMstBridgeInstId
nnMstBridgeInstId.description: Spanning Tree Instance to which the information belongs.

nnMstBridgeVlanMap.name: nnMstBridgeVlanMap
nnMstBridgeVlanMap.description: This gives the bitwise representation for the Vlans Mapped for a particular instance. 512*8 bits used to represent 4096 vlans. The 0th bit represents vlan 1, 1st bit represents vlan 2 and so forth. If vlan n is mapped to a particular instance then the n-1 indexed bit is set
